## PHP output - HTML
In order to embed PHP code with HTML, the PHP must be set apart using PHP start and end tags. 
Note that in the example below, our file is still saved as a .php file

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<h3>The sum of 10 and 5 is </h3>
<?php
$x = 5; // global scope
$y = 10; // global scope
$z = $x + $y; // global scope
echo $z; // output: 15

?>
</body> 
</html>

//Output: The sum of 10 and 5 is 
15